# Code Review Process

## Overview

Our code review process ensures code quality, knowledge sharing, and maintainability through systematic review procedures and clear guidelines.

## Core Concepts

1. **Review Principles**

   - Quality assurance
   - Knowledge sharing
   - Maintainability
   - Team collaboration
   - Continuous improvement

2. **Process Structure**
   - Preparation
   - Review
   - Feedback
   - Resolution

## Implementation

### Pull Request Template

```markdown
## Description

[Description of changes]

## Type of Change

- [ ] Bug fix
- [ ] New feature
- [ ] Breaking change
- [ ] Documentation update

## Testing

- [ ] Unit tests added/updated
- [ ] Integration tests added/updated
- [ ] E2E tests added/updated
- [ ] Manual testing completed

## Checklist

- [ ] Code follows style guidelines
- [ ] Tests passing
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Self-review completed
- [ ] No unnecessary dependencies added
```

// ... existing process sections ...

## Best Practices

### 1. For Authors

- Keep PRs focused and small
- Provide clear descriptions
- Self-review before submission
- Respond promptly to feedback
- Update tests and documentation

### 2. For Reviewers

- Be thorough but timely
- Provide constructive feedback
- Focus on important issues
- Share knowledge
- Consider edge cases

### 3. Code Quality Focus

- Business logic correctness
- Error handling completeness
- Performance implications
- Security considerations
- Maintainability aspects

### 4. Process Efficiency

- Use automated checks
- Follow review checklists
- Maintain clear communication
- Track review metrics
- Regular process improvement

